                            <comment id="17339736" author="mapohl" created="Wed, 5 May 2021 16:00:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;CC &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=fly_in_gis&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;fly_in_gis&quot;&gt;fly_in_gis&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17340152" author="fly_in_gis" created="Thu, 6 May 2021 11:30:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=mapohl&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;mapohl&quot;&gt;mapohl&lt;/a&gt;&#160;Could you share how to reproduce this issue locally? I have run more 100 times and all of them passed without the FATAL error.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17340186" author="mapohl" created="Thu, 6 May 2021 12:45:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I started minikube locally and set &lt;tt&gt;ITCASE_KUBECONFIG&lt;/tt&gt; pointing to my Kubernetes config file within Intellij&apos;s Run Configuration. This enabled the test locally.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17340201" author="till.rohrmann" created="Thu, 6 May 2021 13:14:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think this is a problem of the &lt;tt&gt;TestingLeaderEelctionEventHandler&lt;/tt&gt; which still accepts callbacks after we close the &lt;tt&gt;KubernetesLeaderElectionDriver&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17340611" author="fly_in_gis" created="Fri, 7 May 2021 06:49:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I know why I could not reproduce this issue locally. Because I did not add the &lt;tt&gt;-ea&lt;/tt&gt; VM options when running unit test.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=trohrmann&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;trohrmann&quot;&gt;trohrmann&lt;/a&gt;&#160;is right. The callback in &lt;tt&gt;TestingLeaderEelctionEventHandler&lt;/tt&gt;&#160;could happen even after the &lt;tt&gt;KubernetesLeaderElectionDriver&lt;/tt&gt; is closed. It only happens on the unit test and production codes are not&#160;affected.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
